
[1]litharge

   LITH'ARGE, n. [L. lithargyros, Gr. the spume or scum of silver.

   A semi-vitreous oxyd of lead, produced in refining silver by
   cupellation with lead. It appears in the form of soft flakes, or
   semi-transparent shining plates.
